Date: 0/0/1968
Source: NZ Contemp. Dict. Suppl. (Collins)
Author:
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: <i>compo ... n. </i>workman's compensation for injury incurred while at work [Abbrev. of <i>compensation</i>]; whence<i> off on compo, to go on compo.</i>
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 30
Edition:
Quote: <i>compo</i> compensation for lost wages from work-related injury, formalised as Accident Compensation. <i>- on compo</i> in receipt of such. <i>- compo king</i> malingerer or self-mutilator, with the aim of getting compo. All NZA.
